PLACEHOLDER — security@ PGP public key

This file is a placeholder. Before publishing security.txt / disclosure policy:

  1. Generate a dedicated security@ PGP keypair on an offline/managed machine, e.g.:
       gpg --quick-generate-key "Wisp Security <security@<domain>>" ed25519 sign 2y
  2. Export the PUBLIC key in ASCII-armored form and paste it here, replacing this text:
       gpg --armor --export security@<domain> > pgp-key.asc
  3. Publish the same armored key at https://<domain>/.well-known/pgp-key.asc and reference its
     fingerprint in security.txt.
  4. Keep the PRIVATE key off this repo and out of any build/CI system.

Do NOT commit a private key to this repository.
